# Runbooks

Operational runbooks for the high-traffic MERN URL shortener. Each procedure assumes production access to the Kubernetes namespaces, MongoDB sharded cluster (`mongos` routers), Redis Cluster, Kafka brokers, OpenResty/Nginx (`RedirectEdge`), CDN purge API, and the Express/Node service meshes (`URLService`, `AuthService`, `KGS`, `AnalyticsConsumerGroup`).

---

## Severity Definitions

| Level | Criteria | Response Time |
|-------|----------|---------------|
| **SEV 1** | Redirect loop, origin overload, or complete inability to resolve short URLs. Revenue or brand at immediate risk. | 5 min |
| **SEV 2** | URL mutations (create/update/delete) failing, auth issuance down, analytics pipeline > 1 hr lag, or degraded P99 > 2 s. | 15 min |
| **SEV 3** | Stale CDN cache, partial SLO miss, non-critical consumer lag, or single-node failures with automatic failover already engaged. | 1 hr |

